                <h1>Understanding Auditory Pareidolia: The Sounds You Hear</h1>
                <p>Auditory pareidolia is the phenomenon where the brain perceives familiar sounds or patterns in random noise. Similar to seeing faces in clouds, this intriguing auditory effect can make one hear words, music, or voices in white noise or electronic disturbances. Understanding it reveals the complexities of perception and cognition.</p>
